<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-368-262  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 368 262.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 23 1990 v7 n16 p51(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Interface tool taps features in OS/2 EE. (Intelligent EnvironmentsInc. introduces Applications Manager 2.2 ) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pallatto, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intelligent Environments Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Applications Manager 2.2 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsGraphical User InterfaceProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John PallattoandM;Using the recent delivery of OS/2 Extended Edition 1.2 as a springboard,Intelligent Environments Inc. is now shipping a new version of ApplicationsManager (AM), its interface-design tool, that supports the development ofclient/server database applications.andM;AM 2.2 taps the network-communications capabilities provided in OS/2 ExtendedEdition, delivering direct access to data stored in the IBM Database Managerand in Microsoft Corp.'s SQL Server, according to Terry Golesworthy,president of Intelligent Environments in Tewksbury, Mass.andM;Using AM 2.2, developers can construct an OS/2 Presentation Manager graphicaluser interface for their front-end SQL Server or OS/2 Extended Editionapplications, Golesworthy said.andM;Developers write logic statements and commands in plain English to define theinterface, and AM 2.2 organizes them into a tree structure, automaticallygenerating the Presentation Manager screens, dialogue boxes, list boxes andradio buttons.andM;Intelligent Environments has fine-tuned the new AM version to take advantageof the special features of each database server, Golesworthy said.andM;&quot;Everything that SQL Server supports, we support, including storedprocedures, triggers and access to multiple servers,&quot; he explained.andP;  Storedprocedures are database programs and routines, stored within the server, thatcan execute automatically or at the command of a client workstation.andO;Triggers are special functions programmed into SQL Server to set off events.andM;Along with its support for client/server databases, AM 2.2 also providesimproved 3270 and 5250 terminal emulation and Advanced Peer-to-PeerCommunication (APPC) through IBM's LU 6.2 communications protocol.andP;  Thismeans that developers will be able to build graphical PM interfaces tomainframe applications, including IBM's DB2 database.andM;The company will offer two versions of the AM 2.2 development system: AMProfessional for large applications, priced at $5,000, and AM Personal forsmaller programming projects, priced at $695.andM;Intelligent Environment can be contacted at (508) 640-1080.andO;</TEXT></DOC>